- ♪ Fa la la, la la la, la la la. ♪
- Seriously?

00:14.223 --> 00:17.905
With the Christmas carols? You have been
singing them non stop since Black Friday.

00:17.905 --> 00:20.935
- I'm two seconds away from earplugs.
- It gets me in the spirit.

00:21.055 --> 00:23.170
Besides, you have an art
studio right out there.

00:23.204 --> 00:24.948
It's freezing out there.

00:24.971 --> 00:27.017
Maybe Santa will bring me a space heater.

00:27.017 --> 00:29.670
If you're through being a grinch,

00:29.692 --> 00:32.402
would you mind... shell these for me?

00:32.522 --> 00:34.494
It's peanut brittle time.

00:34.614 --> 00:36.723
You know you can buy them shelled.

00:36.723 --> 00:38.819
No, no, no. They have to be fresh.

00:39.147 --> 00:40.976
- It makes a difference.
- Don't we have enough

00:40.999 --> 00:43.343
with the 11 other kinds
of cookies you're making?

00:43.606 --> 00:46.567
Okay, I know that I go a
little big at Christmas,

00:46.567 --> 00:48.991
but it's the first time since
we've known Daphne and Regina

00:48.991 --> 00:51.162
that they're staying with
us for the holidays, so.

00:51.162 --> 00:52.747
Yeah, usually they're smart enough

00:52.751 --> 00:54.601
to get the hell out of dodge.

00:54.721 --> 00:56.982
Shell.

00:57.472 --> 01:00.857
♪ Fa la la la la, la la la la. ♪

01:00.977 --> 01:03.458
<i>It's not too late to change our plans,</i>

01:03.476 --> 01:05.259
hit the road like we usually do.

01:05.260 --> 01:08.735
World's largest ball of
twine is only 200 miles away.

01:08.855 --> 01:11.118
I definitely want to see that one day,

01:11.152 --> 01:13.898
but it's Christmas. I want
to be with the Kennishes too.

01:13.943 --> 01:15.444
I like the way we do Christmas...

01:15.480 --> 01:17.100
wake up late, open gifts,

01:17.325 --> 01:20.520
sneak Chinese food into
an empty movie theater.

01:20.557 --> 01:23.026
Just promise you'll be nice at dinner.

01:23.630 --> 01:25.866
- Where are we going?
- Sal's.

01:25.900 --> 01:27.618
Sal's with the garlic knots?

01:27.738 --> 01:28.991
I thought that place closed down.

01:29.036 --> 01:30.308
They just reopened.

01:30.428 --> 01:31.986
It's a Christmas miracle!

01:32.106 --> 01:33.774
- Oh, wow!
- (Giggles)

01:33.894 --> 01:36.643
<i>(Music playing faintly)</i>

01:39.875 --> 01:43.683
Thank you. Oh, I don't
know if you got my email,

01:43.718 --> 01:46.296
but we do dinner at 5:00 on the 24th.

01:46.306 --> 01:48.007
And then after dinner,

01:48.127 --> 01:51.775
John reads "The Night Before Christmas"

01:51.802 --> 01:54.830
- and then we open presents.
- Presents on Christmas Eve?

01:54.850 --> 01:56.785
Just one. The rest in the morning.

01:56.819 --> 01:58.260
We start at 8:00.

01:59.055 --> 02:00.217
A.M.?

02:00.337 --> 02:01.923
Sounds great. Right, mom?

02:02.248 --> 02:05.851
After we open the presents, around 11:00...

02:05.860 --> 02:08.376
It takes three hours to open presents?

02:08.496 --> 02:11.110
We don't usually put that
much emphasis on gifts.

02:11.138 --> 02:12.455
Number 62!

02:12.921 --> 02:14.998
Still got your picture on the
wall 'round here somewhere.

02:15.016 --> 02:17.495
Hey, Sal. So glad you reopened, buddy!

02:17.522 --> 02:19.580
How's everything? Can
I get you anything else?

02:19.609 --> 02:22.022
