<i>Bay: This is unbelievable.</i>

18:40.969 --> 18:45.122
Apparently the only time Emmett
and I have been naked together,

18:45.405 --> 18:47.390
rubber duckies were involved.

18:47.510 --> 18:51.497
Ok, I'm telling you, J and
J are about 10 minutes away

18:51.506 --> 18:53.436
from a very conscious uncoupling.

18:53.556 --> 18:55.146
There's one more thing:

18:56.080 --> 18:57.525
Regina's drinking.

18:57.735 --> 18:59.025
Oh no.

18:59.145 --> 19:00.360
Again?

19:00.480 --> 19:02.647
I don't think she ever stopped.

19:02.884 --> 19:04.174
Think about it.

19:04.294 --> 19:07.787
She got sober after she
found out about the switch.

19:07.787 --> 19:09.845
If that never happened?

19:12.773 --> 19:14.428
What is happening there?

19:14.548 --> 19:20.245
_

19:22.915 --> 19:26.363
'Sup? I'm Tobias.

19:27.662 --> 19:29.198
_

19:29.500 --> 19:31.138
- _
- What's with the hand stuff?

19:31.174 --> 19:34.540
This is my friend Daphne.

19:34.832 --> 19:37.567
- She's deaf.
- Whoa. You...

19:37.687 --> 19:39.835
you don't hear anything?

19:41.381 --> 19:44.216
That's... that's profound.

19:44.684 --> 19:46.156
Well,

19:46.276 --> 19:49.824
I'm gonna hit up the Goodwill,
see what they got on vinyl.

19:56.665 --> 19:58.311
Oh, that was weird.

19:58.431 --> 20:00.854
We've got to get out of
this as soon as possible.

20:00.900 --> 20:02.318
What do they do in the movies?

20:02.354 --> 20:05.097
We need to, like, split a fortune cookie

20:05.125 --> 20:09.341
or snap a wishbone or something.

20:09.378 --> 20:10.466
The garlic knots!

20:10.503 --> 20:12.039
- Huh?
- From Sal's!

20:12.076 --> 20:14.015
Don't you remember? You and I were talking

20:14.061 --> 20:15.863
about how much easier life would be

20:15.983 --> 20:17.774
if the switch never happened.

20:17.894 --> 20:19.823
And we split the garlic knot!

20:19.919 --> 20:21.469
Toby said they were magic.

20:21.478 --> 20:23.922
So we have to go back and do it again.

20:23.956 --> 20:25.421
It's Christmas Eve.

20:25.457 --> 20:27.025
He's probably closed.

20:28.640 --> 20:30.028
I have an idea.

20:37.291 --> 20:39.129
This was your great idea?

20:39.147 --> 20:41.205
I was sure they would have

20:41.223 --> 20:43.394
some old garlic knots in here.

20:43.514 --> 20:44.662
Why don't we just wait

20:44.782 --> 20:48.302
for Sal's to reopen after Christmas?

20:49.070 --> 20:51.254
I think it'll be too late.

20:51.288 --> 20:53.745
A Christmas miracle in January?

20:54.038 --> 20:57.523
If it's a Christmas miracle
that undid the switch,

20:57.561 --> 21:00.577
then we need to recreate the moment...

21:00.605 --> 21:04.267
like, get our families
together again and wish it back.

21:04.721 --> 21:06.413
Really wishing I'd watched

21:06.437 --> 21:09.038
more of those stupid movies with my mom.

21:09.852 --> 21:12.074
<i>Man: Ho ho ho!</i>

21:13.099 --> 21:15.077
Are you... ?

21:16.602 --> 21:20.049
It's me. Sal. I dress up for the grandkids.

21:20.315 --> 21:22.611
You girls lose something?

21:25.109 --> 21:28.024
We ate some garlic knots the other night.

21:28.058 --> 21:29.826
Now we've switched places.

21:29.860 --> 21:32.843
Not exactly. We were switched before,

21:32.855 --> 21:36.899
and now we're not switched.
Do you have any more?

21:36.934 --> 21:40.503
Sorry. Gave all the leftovers
to the homeless shelter.

21:43.245 --> 21:44.891
And girls...

21:46.446 --> 21:49.528
The knot's not your answer.

21:49.546 --> 21:50.662
No, it is! It is!

21:50.681 --> 21:52.984
Don't you have the recipe?

21:53.003 --> 21:54.612
Maybe we could just make it ourselves.

21:54.622 --> 21:57.487
- I'm telling you...
- Sal, please!

21:59.356 --> 22:02.314
All right. Wait here.

22:06.383 --> 22:09.548
This is perfect. We'll
just make 'em ourselves.

22:09.668 --> 22:11.334
But if you're right,

22:11.368 --> 22:15.740
and we only have one
night to make this happen,

22:16.115 --> 22:18.877
how are we going to get
our families together?

22:19.334 --> 22:21.759
<i>Regina: Why on earth would
I want to spend Christmas Eve</i>

22:21.795 --> 22:23.652
in snooty Mission Hills?

22:24.146 --> 22:26.048
She's my new friend.

22:26.168 --> 22:28.316
- Who?
- Bay Kennish.

22:28.362 --> 22:30.730
She was nice enough to invite us over.

22:30.754 --> 22:31.965
We have to go.

22:31.983 --> 22:33.890
Wait, Kennish?

22:34.010 --> 22:35.962
Any relation to John Kennish?

22:35.980 --> 22:38.409
Yes! Yes! That's her dad.

22:38.431 --> 22:40.141
You could meet him.

22:40.141 --> 22:42.698
Isn't he the one who's married to...

22:42.733 --> 22:44.064
Kathryn Kennish.

22:44.101 --> 22:46.369
Of Kathryn Kennish Cosmetics.

22:47.183 --> 22:49.562
She's a big deal in the beauty industry.

22:49.571 --> 22:51.446
Who cares? Can we go?

22:53.970 --> 22:55.708
It's a Buckner program.

22:55.828 --> 22:58.150
Adopt a needy family for the holidays.

22:58.270 --> 23:01.058
<i>Toby: I'm with mom. Things are awkward
enough around here on Christmas Eve</i>

23:01.084 --> 23:02.595
without a bunch of strangers around.

23:02.622 --> 23:05.169
Well, they're not exactly strangers.

23:05.192 --> 23:06.592
Daphne's that friend of mine

23:06.712 --> 23:08.291
who's been teaching me sign language.

23:08.325 --> 23:10.159
The one I met?

23:10.193 --> 23:12.171
Yeah. Mom...

23:12.207 --> 23:15.031
Every year you say you
want to do more for charity,

23:15.254 --> 23:16.966
not just give money.

23:17.000 --> 23:18.473
She's right, mom.

23:18.519 --> 23:20.632
It's time the Kennishes start giving back.

23:21.282 --> 23:24.974
Okay, fine. Have them here at 7:00.

23:31.627 --> 23:34.717
<i>Hi! I'm so happy you guys could make it.</i>

23:34.751 --> 23:36.190
They're here!

23:36.310 --> 23:37.462
I'm...

23:37.487 --> 23:38.906
Bay.

23:39.026 --> 23:40.690
Nice to meet you.

23:42.793 --> 23:44.393
This is my dad John,

23:44.428 --> 23:46.864
my mom Kathryn, and my brother Toby.

23:46.900 --> 23:49.432
Mr. Kennish, it's an honor to meet you.

23:49.466 --> 23:50.934
Angelo Sorrento, Jr.

23:50.952 --> 23:53.269
Oh. Hey, Angelo. That's a great name.

23:53.614 --> 23:54.995
I'm a huge fan,

23:54.996 --> 23:57.227
I've never met a
professional athlete before.

23:57.858 --> 23:59.477
Angelo, why don't you come with me?

23:59.487 --> 24:01.654
I can show you a couple of
things from my Royals' days

24:01.682 --> 24:02.979
you might appreciate.

24:06.776 --> 24:08.131
It's nice to meet you.

24:08.148 --> 24:09.986
(Shouting) Thank you!

24:10.020 --> 24:11.871
Merry Christmas!

24:12.849 --> 24:15.245
No matter how loud you yell,

24:15.264 --> 24:17.285
she still can't hear you.

24:17.880 --> 24:19.225
Just

24:19.581 --> 24:21.493
make sure you face her and talk normal...

24:21.521 --> 24:23.551
not too fast, not too slow.

24:23.671 --> 24:24.867
Sorry.

24:24.901 --> 24:28.106
It's okay. Everybody does it.

24:29.773 --> 24:31.788
- You have a lovely home.
- Thank you.

24:31.819 --> 24:35.392
I was just going to go inside and
open a bottle of sauvignon blanc.

24:35.396 --> 24:36.545
You got any scotch?

24:36.580 --> 24:39.415
Yeah, of course. Let's go inside, come on.

24:49.719 --> 24:52.289
Oh, please don't start drinking on me.

24:52.326 --> 24:53.624
Oh, it's Regina's.

24:53.652 --> 24:54.896
I grabbed it when she set it down.

24:54.905 --> 24:57.164
Ah, good thinking. Okay, here.

24:57.284 --> 25:00.191
<i>- Bay: Start rolling this.
- Okay.</i>

25:03.502 --> 25:04.855
Mm...

25:05.165 --> 25:06.899
It's not working.

25:06.934 --> 25:11.011
Ah, we need to put flour down.

25:12.105 --> 25:16.087
<i>♪ ... joyful and triumphant ♪</i>

25:16.207 --> 25:19.782
<i>♪ oh, come ye oh, come ye ♪</i>

25:20.413 --> 25:22.848
Apparently I rock at this.

25:23.193 --> 25:27.501
What is going on? I can
only cook when I'm deaf?

25:27.621 --> 25:29.943
Maybe you were too busy
killing it on the soccer field?

25:29.952 --> 25:34.132
And you grew up with Angelo,
who's amazing in the kitchen.

25:36.171 --> 25:38.037
Oh crap.

25:38.961 --> 25:41.585
We have to drizzle truffle
oil on the garlic knots

25:41.585 --> 25:44.302
when they come out of the
oven. I forgot the truffle oil.

25:44.422 --> 25:47.769
We've gotta have every single thing right.

25:47.889 --> 25:48.903
What are we gonna do?

25:48.930 --> 25:51.377
I'll text Emmett. He owes me a favor.

25:51.411 --> 25:53.346
<i>(Regina laughing)</i>

25:55.561 --> 25:58.433
Oh, you have to tell me how you launched

25:58.442 --> 25:59.549
your own skin care line.

25:59.567 --> 26:01.927
Your products are amazing.
I must have tried them all.

26:02.047 --> 26:03.829
It's not that exciting.

26:03.829 --> 26:06.747
I just saw a need in the
marketplace and I filled it.

26:07.497 --> 26:09.128
So what is it that you do?

26:09.162 --> 26:11.163
- I own a salon.
- Oh.

26:11.198 --> 26:14.233
We're small, but we have
a loyal customer base.

26:14.613 --> 26:17.503
I mean, it's nothing compared
to what you've accomplished.

26:17.540 --> 26:19.470
I've been in the beauty industry

26:19.488 --> 26:21.673
since I was 21. It's in my bones.

26:22.176 --> 26:25.645
So if you were ever looking for
an associate to help you out...

26:27.134 --> 26:29.484
I thought you said you owned a salon.

26:30.179 --> 26:33.060
I do, but...

26:33.654 --> 26:37.523
Business hasn't been so great, actually.

26:37.871 --> 26:40.326
We're shutting our
doors after the holidays.

26:40.707 --> 26:42.695
So the thing is...

26:43.615 --> 26:46.030
I'll keep you in mind if we get an opening.

26:46.048 --> 26:47.347
Ah. Got it.

26:47.374 --> 26:50.137
<i>Kathryn: I, uh, have to
check on the appetizers.</i>

26:50.257 --> 26:52.505
<i>♪ I wanna wish you merry Christmas ♪</i>

26:52.539 --> 26:55.474
<i>♪ and a happy new year ♪</i>

26:55.770 --> 26:57.563
What do you think you're doing?

26:59.479 --> 27:02.081
I just think that you should...

27:02.115 --> 27:03.755
Take it easy, that's all.

27:04.651 --> 27:06.986
You don't know anything about me.

27:07.020 --> 27:08.850
And from the looks of your cushy life,

27:08.859 --> 27:10.798
you don't know anything at all.

27:11.191 --> 27:13.926
You're right. I'm sorry.

27:17.064 --> 27:19.753
It's okay. I get it.

27:19.873 --> 27:22.068
I used to do the same thing with my dad.

27:22.360 --> 27:23.494
You did?

27:23.723 --> 27:24.583
Yeah.

27:24.894 --> 27:27.126
He was a big drinker...

27:28.086 --> 27:30.226
Especially around the holidays.

27:30.346 --> 27:31.909
It got to the point where my mom and I

27:31.918 --> 27:34.451
would just go to a movie on Christmas day

27:34.571 --> 27:36.472
just to get out of the house.

27:37.405 --> 27:40.486
It was the only thing I ever
really liked about Christmas.

27:42.033 --> 27:44.390
- I never knew that.
- How could you?

27:47.723 --> 27:50.768
I can't believe I just told you all that.

27:51.445 --> 27:53.759
I'm gonna go check on A.J.

27:59.832 --> 28:03.115
Oh... I made a lot of food.

28:03.143 --> 28:06.536
We don't need any more, but thank you.

28:06.546 --> 28:07.936
I can understand you.

28:09.116 --> 28:11.164
And I'm happy to do it.

28:11.622 --> 28:12.967
Do you want to help?

28:13.296 --> 28:15.955
Oh, no. No, no, I...

28:16.232 --> 28:17.760
I don't cook.

28:17.997 --> 28:20.741
You don't cook?

28:21.757 --> 28:23.513
Can I tell you a secret?

28:25.350 --> 28:31.240
I bought the entire Christmas
dinner at Whole Foods.

28:31.459 --> 28:36.032
I used to make a big deal about Christmas.

28:37.093 --> 28:42.481
12 kinds of cookies and
homemade peanut brittle.

28:43.817 --> 28:45.951
But no one seemed to care.

28:46.532 --> 28:49.623
And now I'm just too busy.

28:51.489 --> 28:53.492
I bet they did care.

28:54.974 --> 28:57.023
They just didn't show it.

28:59.118 --> 29:00.334
Um...

29:07.249 --> 29:11.877
<i>♪ Hold me tight on Christmas night ♪</i>

29:11.905 --> 29:13.670
<i>♪ this year ♪</i>

29:15.526 --> 29:18.450
Living in silence must be...

29:18.801 --> 29:20.036
Amazing.

29:20.156 --> 29:23.422
Yeah. It has its good points.

29:23.923 --> 29:26.973
I've been thinking about
taking a vow myself.

29:27.243 --> 29:30.875
There's this 30-day program in India.

29:30.884 --> 29:31.753
Uh-huh.

29:31.873 --> 29:34.378
That would be a vow of silence,

29:34.387 --> 29:36.344
not deafness.

29:37.542 --> 29:39.582
This is gonna sound crazy,

29:40.112 --> 29:41.807
but I feel...

29:42.107 --> 29:45.911
This connection to you...

29:47.639 --> 29:49.889
Like we were meant to be together.

29:53.639 --> 29:56.209
I'm only in town for a few days,

29:56.227 --> 29:57.764
but there's this cool teahouse nearby...

29:57.782 --> 29:59.740
<i>- (cell phone vibrates)
- Ooh! (Laughs)</i>

29:59.860 --> 30:01.542
That was my phone, it vibrated.

30:01.569 --> 30:03.188
I got a text message. Ah, see?

30:03.197 --> 30:05.173
Text, and there's... (Clicks tongue)

30:05.293 --> 30:08.467
<i>♪ Hold me tight on Christmas night ♪</i>

30:08.501 --> 30:10.496
<i>♪ this year ♪</i>

30:16.715 --> 30:20.529
_

30:20.922 --> 30:26.840
_

30:27.086 --> 30:28.724
_

30:29.382 --> 30:32.346
_

30:32.995 --> 30:36.233
_

30:53.947 --> 30:57.196
So what is it? Am I too East Riverside?

30:57.214 --> 30:58.504
Okay, this is ridiculous.

30:58.624 --> 31:02.053
I invite you into my home on Christmas Eve,

31:02.071 --> 31:03.799
we adopt you for the holidays

31:03.836 --> 31:05.556
and now you're hitting me up for a job?

31:05.565 --> 31:07.056
Adopt us?

31:07.074 --> 31:10.220
My daughter said you invited us
because our girls were friends.

31:10.257 --> 31:12.470
- Hey, guys, guys.
- We don't need to be adopted.

31:12.470 --> 31:14.116
<i>- I'll be adopted by them.
- A.J.!</i>

31:14.126 --> 31:15.369
- You know what?
- What?!

31:15.370 --> 31:17.126
Could you please hold on five minutes?

31:17.246 --> 31:19.084
Just five more minutes.

31:19.204 --> 31:20.606
Fine.

31:20.640 --> 31:21.707
(Scoffs)

31:22.240 --> 31:23.602
Mom...

31:26.676 --> 31:28.871
Hey, sorry to interrupt, hi, Emmett.

31:31.377 --> 31:33.911
This is Daphne. No wait. I'm Daphne.

31:33.957 --> 31:36.893
This is Bay. I'm teaching
her sign language.

31:36.911 --> 31:39.911
Okay, yeah, so, uh... things are starting
to get a little bit crazy in there.

31:39.938 --> 31:42.545
So if we're gonna do
this, we need to do it now.

31:43.176 --> 31:45.097
_

31:45.133 --> 31:46.779
_

31:48.746 --> 31:50.923
We've overstayed our welcome.

31:50.959 --> 31:53.713
- Wait!
- John: Bay, I really think it's best we let them go.

31:53.713 --> 31:55.890
Who's ready for some garlic knots?

31:55.935 --> 31:58.231
You have to try one. They're magic.

32:00.784 --> 32:03.656
- What are you doing?
- It's now or never.

32:05.558 --> 32:08.585
Both: I wish we'd been switched at birth!

32:18.189 --> 32:19.698
Excuse me?

32:19.818 --> 32:21.834
What did you two just say?

32:21.954 --> 32:23.702
Nothing happened.

32:23.978 --> 32:28.634
_

32:28.899 --> 32:31.295
Daphne Paloma Sorrento,
go and get your coat.

32:31.415 --> 32:32.785
<i>We'll be waiting in the car.</i>

32:32.905 --> 32:35.502
A.J.? Excuse me.

32:44.008 --> 32:46.652
♪ A snowflake fell ♪

32:47.219 --> 32:50.127
<i>♪ And came to see ♪</i>

32:50.913 --> 32:53.630
<i>♪ his crystal bones ♪</i>

32:54.269 --> 32:56.894
<i>- ♪ and filigree ♪
- Hi, Daphne.</i>

32:56.922 --> 32:59.602
<i>♪ He said every snowflake's different ♪</i>

32:59.648 --> 33:02.483
Bay is not here. She just left.

33:02.603 --> 33:04.923
- You might be able to catch...
- It's okay.

33:04.957 --> 33:06.658
I came to see you.

33:07.661 --> 33:08.758
Oh.

33:08.878 --> 33:10.569
I'm really sorry that we ruined

33:10.606 --> 33:13.139
- your Christmas Eve last night.
- Oh.

33:13.259 --> 33:15.867
No, honey. You didn't.

33:17.658 --> 33:20.557
<i>♪ Above the rooftops ♪</i>

33:20.677 --> 33:22.020
For me?

33:23.337 --> 33:26.209
<i>♪ As long as we're together ♪</i>

33:26.329 --> 33:30.023
<i>♪ things will turn out right ♪</i>

33:30.143 --> 33:33.421
<i>- ♪ they held each other closer ♪
- Is this for...</i>

33:33.541 --> 33:35.571
Making peanut brittle?

33:39.065 --> 33:42.285
And you brought peanuts in the shell.

33:42.742 --> 33:44.672
It makes a difference.

33:47.361 --> 33:49.374
Come on in.

33:49.494 --> 33:52.017
<i>♪ We were cut from the same paper ♪</i>

33:52.062 --> 33:55.127
<i>♪ that was folded long ago ♪</i>

33:55.172 --> 33:58.675
<i>♪ so before we hit the
ground and turn to snow ♪</i>

33:58.795 --> 34:01.135
<i>(Knocks on door)</i>

34:02.700 --> 34:06.257
<i>♪ Won't you melt into my arms ♪</i>

34:06.294 --> 34:08.360
<i>♪ before we go... ♪</i>

34:08.481 --> 34:10.565
Hi. Um,

34:10.821 --> 34:13.775
- Daphne just ran off somewhere.
- That's okay.

34:14.351 --> 34:17.168
Look, I know we don't know each other well,

34:17.289 --> 34:20.241
but I just wanted to say
I'm sorry for last night.

34:20.799 --> 34:23.688
No, no, I'm the one who's sorry.

34:23.809 --> 34:26.342
I shouldn't have hit
your mom up for a job...

34:26.462 --> 34:29.607
And I definitely shouldn't
have drank so much.

34:30.741 --> 34:33.558
It's just tomato juice. I swear.

34:34.409 --> 34:36.748
I came to tell you...

34:38.780 --> 34:40.628
I knew someone once...

34:41.341 --> 34:43.426
someone I was close to...

34:43.545 --> 34:46.500
she went through a really hard time...

34:46.847 --> 34:49.498
But she kicked it.

34:49.619 --> 34:51.429
She got sober.

34:53.524 --> 34:55.938
I'm sure that you could too.

34:56.826 --> 34:59.122
I'm sure your kids would be there for you.

35:02.699 --> 35:04.227
Thank you.

35:04.611 --> 35:07.519
And, um, I brought something.

35:12.138 --> 35:14.407
I thought maybe we could watch it together.

35:18.121 --> 35:21.163
Don't you have some fancy Christmas thing

35:21.166 --> 35:22.602
at your parents' house?

35:23.123 --> 35:26.831
Yeah, but I'd rather do this.

35:28.903 --> 35:31.885
I'm sorry, I don't have any food.

35:32.242 --> 35:34.705
- Maybe we could order some Chinese?
- Oh, that's okay.

35:35.416 --> 35:38.041
Wait for Daphne to come back? Could be fun.

35:40.849 --> 35:44.325
Might be. Come on in.

36:08.399 --> 36:11.490
(Off-key) La la la.

36:11.838 --> 36:13.594
Yes!

36:13.850 --> 36:16.155
<i>(Clock chiming)</i>

36:23.417 --> 36:27.826
Oh, I am so happy to see
your chipmunk-y little faces.

36:30.269 --> 36:33.360
- Merry Christmas.
- Hi!

36:33.480 --> 36:35.308
Hi.

36:42.369 --> 36:45.122
The whole perfect-Kennish-Christmas thing

36:45.140 --> 36:47.481
makes me feel like you were cheated

36:47.482 --> 36:49.448
out of this storybook life...

36:49.467 --> 36:53.171
like you somehow drew the short
straw because you got stuck

36:53.171 --> 36:55.302
- with the single mom...
- Mom.

36:56.066 --> 36:58.737
I love our Christmases.

36:58.857 --> 37:00.191
Really?

37:01.664 --> 37:03.155
Really.

37:05.752 --> 37:07.481
Okay.

37:11.954 --> 37:13.810
- Morning.
- Mommy!

37:14.570 --> 37:16.243
"Mommy?"

37:16.481 --> 37:18.256
- Is it Christmas?
- Yes.

37:18.376 --> 37:20.634
Okay, I wanna make gingerbread pancakes

37:20.652 --> 37:23.990
and then I want you to sing
Christmas Carols all day long.

37:24.036 --> 37:26.021
Oh, and baking! I want to bake!

37:26.039 --> 37:31.179
Honey, stop, please. I know that you
and I are really, really different.

37:31.188 --> 37:34.343
We always have been. I love
all this stuff and you don't.

37:34.361 --> 37:36.876
- I need to stop forcing it on you.
- Mom,

37:37.178 --> 37:40.727
I love every single thing
about our Christmases.

37:42.163 --> 37:43.836
That's not entirely true,

37:43.882 --> 37:47.924
but every family has a little crazy.

37:48.299 --> 37:50.897
And if I have to have crazy,

37:51.802 --> 37:54.620
I prefer your crazy over anyone else's.

37:54.740 --> 37:56.595
Come here, honey.

37:57.190 --> 37:58.882
<i>(Door opens)</i>

37:59.156 --> 38:01.918
- Hi. Hi.
- Merry Christmas!

38:02.870 --> 38:05.595
There's some moo shu pork,

38:05.622 --> 38:07.442
some vegetable chow mein,

38:07.460 --> 38:09.490
and a whole lot of egg rolls

38:09.500 --> 38:12.125
being delivered any minute.

38:12.653 --> 38:15.726
- So...
- Kathryn. Thank you.

38:15.846 --> 38:19.028
- So much.
- Ho ho ho.

38:19.339 --> 38:21.754
Let's open some presents, all right?!

38:21.754 --> 38:23.528
Yes!

38:24.954 --> 38:29.061
Hey, did those garlic knots
do anything weird to you?

38:29.080 --> 38:31.769
Because I had the strangest

38:31.796 --> 38:33.580
- dream last night.
- Me too!

38:33.589 --> 38:36.260
Me too! Um...

38:36.498 --> 38:38.445
- You and I...
- Oh, no.

38:38.464 --> 38:40.668
Were, um... oh, it was so weird.

38:41.198 --> 38:42.854
We were skydiving!

38:42.881 --> 38:46.631
(Gasps) Skydiving!

38:46.751 --> 38:48.845
Skydiving is good!

38:49.119 --> 38:50.903
<i>John: Toby, Bay,</i>

38:51.023 --> 38:53.510
so tell them about the Christmas

38:53.630 --> 38:56.272
when your mom set me on fire.

38:56.392 --> 38:58.193
<i>- Kathryn: No, no, no, no, no.
- What?!</i>

38:58.485 --> 39:01.192
<i>I did not set him on fire!</i>

39:01.201 --> 39:03.744
<i>- John: What are you talking about?
- Well... just accidentally.</i>

39:04.549 --> 39:07.766
So we're at the candlelight service...

39:07.768 --> 39:10.692
And everyone is singing "Silent Night"...

39:10.695 --> 39:12.757
<i>John: And, you know,
they're passing the flame</i>

39:12.791 --> 39:14.290
from person to person...

39:14.317 --> 39:17.071
And mom hands it to dad

39:17.080 --> 39:18.853
and accidentally just...

39:18.973 --> 39:21.076
- Both: Whoosh!
- No!

39:21.122 --> 39:22.842
- (Gasps)
- Up my arm, down my back,

39:22.869 --> 39:24.790
down the other arm, and I'm like, "ahhh!"

39:24.836 --> 39:27.800
And then all of a sudden,
the flames... gone.

39:27.920 --> 39:29.913
- What?
- Because the sweater

39:29.940 --> 39:32.967
- was flame retardant.
- (All laugh)

39:34.815 --> 39:37.321
It was awesome. You should've seen it.

39:45.819 --> 39:49.360
I can't believe we missed all
these Christmases together.

39:54.883 --> 39:56.567
We're together now.

40:00.939 --> 40:06.377
♪ Have yourself a
merry little Christmas ♪

40:06.866 --> 40:12.225
♪ let your heart be light ♪

40:12.747 --> 40:16.604
♪ from now on, our troubles ♪

40:16.607 --> 40:22.026
♪ will be out of sight... ♪

40:22.060 --> 40:23.961
- Your turn.
- That's beautiful.

40:23.995 --> 40:24.977
<i>(Kathryn laughs)</i>

40:25.097 --> 40:30.067
♪ Have yourself a
merry little Christmas ♪

40:30.463 --> 40:35.206
♪ make the yuletide gay ♪

40:35.813 --> 40:38.657
Both: ♪ from now on ♪

40:38.693 --> 40:43.981
♪ our troubles will be miles away... ♪

40:47.071 --> 40:48.635
Your turn.

40:48.873 --> 40:53.556
♪ Here we are as in olden days ♪

40:53.676 --> 40:59.163
♪ happy golden days of yore ♪

41:00.763 --> 41:06.036
All: ♪ faithful friends
who are dear to us ♪

41:06.156 --> 41:09.571
♪ gather near to us ♪

41:09.691 --> 41:11.857
♪ once more... ♪

41:12.059 --> 41:13.166
- Oh, no.
- No.

41:13.184 --> 41:15.461
<i>Toby: Come on.</i>

41:15.736 --> 41:21.498
(Discordant) ♪ through the
years, we all will be together ♪

41:21.544 --> 41:26.538
♪ if the fates allow ♪

41:26.913 --> 41:30.772
♪ hang a shining star ♪

41:30.809 --> 41:35.199
♪ upon the highest bough ♪

41:38.803 --> 41:43.092
All: ♪ and have yourself ♪

41:43.212 --> 41:48.168
♪ a merry little Christmas ♪

41:48.288 --> 41:49.796
♪ now. ♪

41:49.916 --> 41:51.507
(Laughing)

41:51.552 --> 41:54.118
- Oh.
- (All cheer)

